   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Indicator 1.1: # of dedicated officers in MWCSD to monitor effectiveness of communications campaign 
Indicator 2.1: Number of households in Samoa reached by mobile blasts and radio spots.</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2019">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">Baseline 1.1: One dedicated officer in MWCSD 
Baseline 2.1: 0 households reached by mobile blasts and dedicated radio spots</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Target 1.1. Statistician hired and seconded to the Policy and Research Division of the MWCSD for data and information gathering during and after the campaign.
Target  2.1. Mobile text blasts sent out to all DIGICEL and BLUESKY customers, which is about 90% of the population (195,843, 2017 Population Census), reaching even the most isolated families.

Target  2.2. Airing of messaging on radio networks.
Target  2.3. Transportation and access to isolated families provided.

Target 3.1. Hiring of short-term local surge capacity (21 working days).</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output 1. Augmentation of coordination efforts by the MWCSD through embedding of technical capacity in the Ministry focusing on Monitoring and Evaluation of the community awareness raising campaign, through the conduct of an impact study
Output 2.  Rapidity of anti-measles messaging reaching the general public enhanced through effective use of digital means to prevent the spread of the measles disease

Output 3.  UNDP Samoa&#x2019;s capacity for coordination and liaison as well as reporting on UNDP&#x2019;s contribution to the One UN measles response strengthened.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">OUTPUT 1	
1.1	Two Dedicated Officers in MWCSD for 20 Days


OUTPUT 2	

2.1	100% of Households in Samoa reached through Rapidity Anti-Measles Messaging</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNDP supported the Ministry of Women, Community and Social Development to conduct an impact assessment of the Community Development Sector Response Awareness Campaign conducted during the recent measles epidemic in Q4. The impact assessment shows that there has been an increase in the public&#x2019;s level of awareness and understanding on measles. Moreover, evidence highlights that delivering awareness campaigns through the use  of  a  combination  of  means  of  communication  is  more  effective than  distributing  printed  materials.  Furthermore,  the  assessment  found  that  the  messages received by the informants were helpful in understanding facts about measles and the importance of vaccination. The lessons from the impact assessment were absorbed by the Ministry to inform the COVID community outreach and awareness campaign.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
